4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING GAMBLING LAWS TO ALLOW NONPROFIT
5 ORGANIZATIONS, COLLEGES, UNIVERSITIES, AND SCHOOL DISTRICTS TO USE CREDIT CARDS FOR
6 RAFFLES; REVISING THE DESCRIPTION OF "CREDIT GAMBLING" AND THE DEFINITION OF "INTERNET
7 GAMBLING" TO ALLOW CERTAIN ENTITIES TO USE CREDIT CARDS FOR RAFFLES; AMENDING
8 SECTIONS 23-5-112, 23-5-157, AND 23-5-413, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
