5 Section 3. Section 23-5-413, MCA, is amended to read:
6 "23-5-413. Raffle prizes -- investigations -- rulemaking. (1) (a) The department shall investigate all
7 violations of this part.
8 (b) The department may adopt rules to require recordkeeping for receipts and payouts under this
9 part and to establish procedures to ensure the fair selection of winners.
10 (2) (a) A person or organization conducting a raffle shall own all prizes to be awarded as part of
11 the raffle before the sale of any tickets.
12 (b) The value of a prize awarded for an individual ticket for a raffle conducted by a person or an
13 organization may not exceed $5,000. Prizes may not be combined in any manner to increase the ultimate value
14 of the prize awarded for each ticket.
15 (c) The provisions of subsections (2)(a) and (2)(b) do not apply to a nonprofit organization, a
16 college, a university, a public school district as provided in 20-6-101 and 20-6-701, or a nonpublic school as
17 described in 20-5-102(2)(e). The proceeds from the sale of tickets for a raffle conducted by a nonprofit
18 organization, college, university, or school district may be used only for charitable purposes or to pay for prizes
19 and may not be used for the administrative costs of conducting the raffle.
20 (3) (a) The sale of raffle tickets authorized by this part is restricted to events and participants within
21 the geographic confines of the state. Nonprofit organizations may sell raffle tickets outside the state of Montana
22 if the purchase is not prohibited in the jurisdiction in which the purchaser resides.
23 (b) Except raffles sponsored by nonprofit organizations, the sale of raffle tickets may not be
24 conducted over the internet. All raffle announcements or advertisements conducted over the internet must
25 include this sale restriction, the name of the organization offering the raffle, and all raffle terms.
26 (c) Except for a raffle sponsored by a nonprofit organization, college, university, or school district,
27 the sale of a raffle ticket may not be purchased with a credit card."
